    5.0 out of 5 starsValue that's Impressive, eye-catching, and unique
    ByRitchieon December 6, 2016
    Color: A: Chakra|Verified Purchase
    This item came quickly in the mail, and was securely packaged.

    Upon opening the black pouch, within which it was contained, I noticed it came with a longer bonus chain, to my surprise. (see picture) I appreciate that they have lobster claw clasps, and they seem durable and appropriate for the pendant. I have yet to wear this item, so I can't attest to its durability or if there will be any skin reaction but I'm initially impressed by its unique appeal. The product picture doesn't really show it, but the "tree" is composed of two-different colored wires, which lends a lovely affect. I can't confirm that the stones are authentic but they are lovely on the necklace. I appreciate how the necklace is designed so that the pendant will lie flat against one's chest, with the stones protruding mainly on side (see picture); this does mean, though, that the preferred lie of the pendant upon one's chest is predetermined. Running my hand along the pendant, I do not initially feel any wires poking or tugging; the stones seem secure, too.

    If I have any problems upon wearing this item, I will try to remember to update this review but for now, I'm VERY pleased with this purchase. I could see this as being a nice gift to give to someone, too.

    Update: 5-star rating remains. (...and not because of statement on back of the company's packaging.)
    Every time I wear this, I receive compliments and inquiries. It is very comfortable to wear, without excessively moving, and it "plays nicely," for the most part, with my clothing. (Note: I wore it with a finely woven shirt that it did tug at a bit, but I have problems with this blouse, no matter what necklace/pendant I wear.) I have not yet noticed any discoloration to my skin or clothing, from this piece, nor have I noticed any fading/peeling/dulling/etc of the piece, itself. The stones and wiring have remained secure beautifully, too. This is a wonderful piece.

    5.0 out of 5 starsA beautiful pendant - I would recommend it to others
    ByJoan Mon June 14, 2017
    Color: A: Chakra|Verified Purchase
    This is beautiful! I've admired the Tree of Life pendants for a while now, glad I finally got around to ordering.

    * The pendant is 2 inches in diameter, larger than I expected.
    * The chain is 32 inches (hangs down 16 inches)
    * The second chain (surprise!) is 20 inches (hangs 10 inches) long and a finer link than the longer chain.
    * Both chains are a copper color - unusual, but I like it.
    ** It looks like a few of the stones may be drilled a little too close to the edge and so may break off if bumped hard or caught on something...I'll have to be careful. I'll try to update this review after a while to let you know about this possible issue.
    ** I noticed one rough spot, at the end of the loop that attaches the pendant on the chain. Should be easily filed with a nail file; isn't catching on my top either way - I had to actively look for rough spots.

    I almost forgot to mention the packaging. The Pedant is on a card with the chain behind to prevent tangles, in a small plastic bag (easily opened, but "sealed." This is found inside a black microfiber (?) drawstring pouch, all enclosed in another plastic bag. This was in a bubble wrap/manila envelope. Well protected but easily opened upon receipt. And it was received quickly - just three days from order date!

    I'm glad I made this purchase and would recommend it to others.
